1058
00:48:57,210 --> 00:48:58,867
- Hello, Steve.

1059
00:48:58,950 --> 00:49:00,997
This is Jasper coukos.

1060
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:04,417
You sold me an exciting
life insurance policy recently

1061
00:49:04,500 --> 00:49:06,967
and said that if I had
any questions to call you.

1062
00:49:07,050 --> 00:49:08,377
- Oh, sure, sure, Mr. Coukos.

1063
00:49:08,460 --> 00:49:09,517
What's on your mind?

1064
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:13,140
- I'd like for you to tell
me how to raise the dead.

1065
00:49:13,223 --> 00:49:15,577
- (Laughs) Very funny, Mr. Coukos.

1066
00:49:15,660 --> 00:49:16,987
Anyone in particular?

1067
00:49:17,070 --> 00:49:19,117
- Well, it's a witch
named hepzibah Crowley.

1068
00:49:19,200 --> 00:49:22,087
You see, she's put a curse on my family.

1069
00:49:22,170 --> 00:49:23,677
And it was my thought that if we could,

1070
00:49:23,760 --> 00:49:25,246
well, bring her back to life,

1071
00:49:25,329 --> 00:49:28,833
that we could possibly talk
her into removing the curse.

1072
00:49:30,510 --> 00:49:31,807
- Well, Mr. Coukos,

1073
00:49:31,890 --> 00:49:33,967
I really don't have
time for practical jokes.

1074
00:49:34,050 --> 00:49:35,917
- Oh, I'm quite serious about this.

1075
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:38,737
You did say I could ask you anything.

1076
00:49:38,820 --> 00:49:40,717
- But not about raising the dead.

1077
00:49:40,800 --> 00:49:42,517
I don't know that.

1078
00:49:42,600 --> 00:49:45,176
- Well, Steve, if that's the case,

1079
00:49:45,259 --> 00:49:49,087
I'd better cancel my
policy with your company

1080
00:49:49,170 --> 00:49:50,917
if you can't answer my questions.

1081
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:52,495
- No, don't do that.

1082
00:49:52,578 --> 00:49:53,587
Hold on.

1083
00:49:53,670 --> 00:49:55,443
I'll look this up in my file.

1084
00:49:59,610 --> 00:50:01,717
Yes, Mr. Coukos, raising the dead.

1085
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:04,117
I have that here in my
worksheet right now, yes.

1086
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:05,250
Do you have a pencil?

1087
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:09,817
Good, well, you take a
bottle of witch Hazel, yes.

1088
00:50:09,900 --> 00:50:11,107
And then dump it all over the ground.

1089
00:50:11,190 --> 00:50:12,483
And then you buy a book.

1090
00:50:14,017 --> 00:50:16,237
"The house of seven
gables," that's the book.

1091
00:50:16,320 --> 00:50:19,867
And you read it backwards and very fast.

1092
00:50:19,950 --> 00:50:21,127
Very fast and backwards.

1093
00:50:21,210 --> 00:50:24,277
And then if that doesn't bring
her back, well, nothing will.

1094
00:50:24,360 --> 00:50:27,170
- Well, that sounds easy enough.

1095
00:50:27,253 --> 00:50:29,287
Thank you for your help, Steve.

1096
00:50:29,370 --> 00:50:31,203
- Not at all, anytime.

1097
00:50:33,780 --> 00:50:35,193
Crazy son of a bitch.

1098
00:50:36,480 --> 00:50:38,827
- So Kerry also acted strangely

1099
00:50:38,910 --> 00:50:40,417
when you took the blindfold off.

1100
00:50:40,500 --> 00:50:43,627
- Right, and she had a big red nose.

1101
00:50:43,710 --> 00:50:45,517
- This is very interesting.

1102
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:47,197
Do you see the pattern?

1103
00:50:47,280 --> 00:50:50,587
To you, everybody else seems
insane when you look at them,

1104
00:50:50,670 --> 00:50:53,047
but you feel perfectly normal.

1105
00:50:53,130 --> 00:50:55,897
This may be a projection
of your own insanity

1106
00:50:55,980 --> 00:50:57,997
onto everybody else.

1107
00:50:58,080 --> 00:50:59,935
Because you can't face the reality,

1108
00:51:00,018 --> 00:51:02,643
which is that you are
the one with the problem.

