00:52:28,260 --> 00:52:29,428
From the ruinous porch
seemed to hear the bell sound

1145
00:52:29,511 --> 00:52:30,474
incredibly well.

1146
00:52:30,557 --> 00:52:34,546
(Jasper reading indistinctly)

1147
00:52:34,629 --> 00:52:37,296
(Witch wailing)

1148
00:52:39,073 --> 00:52:39,932
(Smoke hissing)

1149
00:52:40,015 --> 00:52:42,682
(Witch wailing)

1150
00:52:46,724 --> 00:52:48,615
- Hey, lady, lady, what's wrong?

1151
00:52:48,698 --> 00:52:51,000
Where did you come from?

1152
00:52:51,083 --> 00:52:52,602
- Where am I?

1153
00:52:52,685 --> 00:52:53,617
Who are you?

1154
00:52:53,700 --> 00:52:55,387
- I'm Sam Lindquist, judge Lindquist.

1155
00:52:55,470 --> 00:52:56,227
- Judge?

1156
00:52:56,310 --> 00:52:57,337
Not another judge.

1157
00:52:57,420 --> 00:52:59,538
- I'm the only judge in these parts.

1158
00:52:59,621 --> 00:53:02,739
- This is not my time.

1159
00:53:02,822 --> 00:53:04,537
- What time?

1160
00:53:04,620 --> 00:53:06,037
What's the last thing you remember?

1161
00:53:06,120 --> 00:53:08,797
- I was burning at the stake.

1162
00:53:08,880 --> 00:53:12,037
Then I heard some idiot
reading something backwards.

1163
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:14,304
- Come inside, I'll call
someone that can help you.

1164
00:53:14,387 --> 00:53:17,107
- You'll call no one on my behalf.

1165
00:53:17,190 --> 00:53:19,267
I trust no judge!

1166
00:53:19,350 --> 00:53:23,222
I'll be bound you condemned
many to death or imprisonment.

1167
00:53:23,305 --> 00:53:24,517
- No, not many.

1168
00:53:24,600 --> 00:53:27,847
Most of of my cases are
civil cases, small claims.

1169
00:53:27,930 --> 00:53:30,242
- I can hear your voice now.

1170
00:53:30,325 --> 00:53:34,537
I condemn thee to burn
at the stake until dead.

1171
00:53:34,620 --> 00:53:37,897
I condemn thee to hang until dead.

1172
00:53:37,980 --> 00:53:39,607
- I do no such thing.

1173
00:53:39,690 --> 00:53:40,807
Come inside, please.

1174
00:53:40,890 --> 00:53:41,767
We'll talk this over.

1175
00:53:41,850 --> 00:53:45,398
- Judges love to hear the
sound of their own voices.

1176
00:53:45,481 --> 00:53:48,307
How many witches did you put to death?

1177
00:53:48,390 --> 00:53:50,367
- Lady, there are no such thing as witches.

1178
00:53:50,450 --> 00:53:52,447
- No such thing as witches?

1179
00:53:52,530 --> 00:53:54,697
I, hepzibah Crowley, am a witch.

1180
00:53:54,780 --> 00:53:56,406
A most powerful witch!

1181
00:53:56,489 --> 00:54:00,564
I'll teach you the truth about witches.

1182
00:54:00,647 --> 00:54:02,467
- Lady, come inside.

1183
00:54:02,550 --> 00:54:05,737
Please, you need help,
everything will be all right.

1184
00:54:05,820 --> 00:54:07,897
- I'll fix that voice of yours.

1185
00:54:07,980 --> 00:54:11,376
I'll make you the laughing
stock of the county.

1186
00:54:11,459 --> 00:54:12,396
(Dramatic music)

1187
00:54:12,479 --> 00:54:14,207
(Judge coughs)

1188
00:54:14,290 --> 00:54:17,117
Wait, wait, come back here!

1189
00:54:17,200 --> 00:54:19,355
My voice, something's happened to my voice.

1190
00:54:19,438 --> 00:54:21,573
I've got a big case tomorrow!

1191
00:54:23,835 --> 00:54:26,617
- I remember all.

1192
00:54:26,700 --> 00:54:28,131
The loons!

1193
00:54:28,214 --> 00:54:31,057
(Laughs) Powers of darkness,

1194
00:54:31,140 --> 00:54:33,633
bring me to the last of the loons!

1195
00:54:35,770 --> 00:54:39,097
(Thunder cracks)

1196
00:54:39,180 --> 00:54:40,417
- Everything will be okay, June.

1197
00:54:40,500 --> 00:54:42,991
You'll see. - Oh, poor Jeff.

1198
00:54:43,074 --> 00:54:44,463
I warned him.

1199
00:54:44,546 --> 00:54:46,593
I only tried to do what was right.

1200
00:54:48,090 --> 00:54:49,233
Where's Jasper?

1201
00:54:50,073 --> 00:54:53,137
Ah, I told him to stay here!

1202
00:54:53,220 --> 00:54:53,977
- He'll be back.

1203
00:54:54,060 --> 00:54:55,707
Everything will be okay, you'll see.

1204
00:54:55,790 --> 00:54:58,837
(Eerie music)

1205
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:00,998
- Where is the last of the loons?

1206
00:55:01,081 --> 00:55:03,727
(Thunder cracks)

1207
00:55:03,810 --> 00:55:04,930
Where is

1208
00:55:06,330 --> 00:55:07,163
everybody?

1209
00:55:09,030 --> 00:55:10,417
- Who in blue blazes are you?

1210
00:55:10,500 --> 00:55:12,745
- From blue blazes, I come.

1211
00:55:12,828 --> 00:55:16,657
I am hepzibah Crowley. - As in witch?

1212
00:55:16,740 --> 00:55:18,003
- It is so.

1213
00:55:19,740 --> 00:55:21,607
- What a surprise.

1214
00:55:21,690 --> 00:55:22,897
Make yourself at home.

1215
00:55:22,980 --> 00:55:25,477
Kerry and I were just heading out the door

1216
00:55:25,560 --> 00:55:26,947
to buy airline tickets.

1217
00:55:27,030 --> 00:55:28,117
- Airplanes, who needs airplanes?

1218
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,887
My car has a full tank.

1219
00:55:29,970 --> 00:55:31,507
- Stay where you are.

1220
00:55:31,590 --> 00:55:34,147
Tell me where the last of the loons are.

1221
00:55:34,230 --> 00:55:35,917
- Why, hello everyone.

1222
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:37,387
Why, who's that person there?

1223
00:55:37,470 --> 00:55:38,917
- Witch. - That one right there.

1224
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:39,750
- Witch!

1225
00:55:39,833 --> 00:55:41,737
- I said which one,
that person right there.

1226
00:55:41,820 --> 00:55:43,507
- It's a witch, Jasper.

1227
00:55:43,590 --> 00:55:45,007
The witch, get it!

1228
00:55:45,090 --> 00:55:45,923
- Oh.

1229
00:55:46,890 --> 00:55:49,957
- A loon, I know it is so.

1230
00:55:50,040 --> 00:55:52,237
I am hepzibah Crowley.

1231
00:55:52,320 --> 00:55:53,676
- Oh, well this is a surprise.

1232
00:55:53,759 --> 00:55:55,597
I didn't think it worked.

1233
00:55:55,680 --> 00:55:58,297
- Then it was you who
raised me from the grave?

1234
00:55:58,380 --> 00:55:59,213
- Yes.

1235
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:03,817
- Oh, then you have fallen to the curse.

1236
00:56:03,900 --> 00:56:07,237
Only a madman would
bring me back from the dead.

1237
00:56:07,320 --> 00:56:10,567
- No, no, I was mad, but I'm very sane now.

1238
00:56:10,650 --> 00:56:11,400
Very sane.

1239
00:56:11,483 --> 00:56:13,777
Besides, I can't take
all the credit for this.

1240
00:56:13,860 --> 00:56:17,557
It was Steve weevil who
told me how to raise the dead.

1241
00:56:17,640 --> 00:56:19,567
- Steve weevil.

1242
00:56:19,650 --> 00:56:22,387
My insurance man knows
how to raise the dead?

1243
00:56:22,470 --> 00:56:24,667
Boy, they'll do anything
to avoid paying a claim.

1244
00:56:24,750 --> 00:56:27,637
- Where can I find this powerful warlock?

1245
00:56:27,720 --> 00:56:29,583
- Well, here's his card right there.

1246
00:56:30,463 --> 00:56:33,247
- I'll be back for you.

1247
00:56:33,330 --> 00:56:34,477
- Fine, we'll brew some coffee.

1248
00:56:34,560 --> 00:56:35,410
Won't we, mother?

1249
00:56:36,307 --> 00:56:38,807
(Eerie music)

1250
00:56:48,933 --> 00:56:51,683
(Pages rustling)

1251
00:56:54,599 --> 00:56:57,617
(Steve shouts)

1252
00:56:57,700 --> 00:56:59,407
- Who the hell are you?

1253
00:56:59,490 --> 00:57:02,437
- You mean who from hell are you?

1254
00:57:02,520 --> 00:57:04,804
- Lady, how the hell did you get in here?

1255
00:57:04,887 --> 00:57:07,987
- You are the one called Steve weevil?

1256
00:57:08,070 --> 00:57:09,697
- Yeah, I am the one.

1257
00:57:09,780 --> 00:57:10,605
Which one are you?

1258
00:57:10,688 --> 00:57:14,673
- I am hepzibah Crowley, a witch.

1259
00:57:14,756 --> 00:57:19,147
You knew of the spell that
would raise me from my grave?

1260
00:57:19,230 --> 00:57:22,237
Just how powerful a warlock are you?

1261
00:57:22,320 --> 00:57:25,177
- Lady, I don't have
the tiniest, smallest idea

1262
00:57:25,260 --> 00:57:27,340
