00:59:23,100 --> 00:59:28,100
But as for the other,
I know not what he is.

1303
00:59:28,380 --> 00:59:31,417
- He was insane, at birth.

1304
00:59:31,500 --> 00:59:33,397
But the curse worked backwards.

1305
00:59:33,480 --> 00:59:35,257
He went sane at his last birthday.

1306
00:59:35,340 --> 00:59:38,553
- So my revenge is not yet complete.

1307
00:59:39,540 --> 00:59:40,482
Very well.

1308
00:59:40,565 --> 00:59:45,307
The last of the loons will
suffer the same fate as I did.

1309
00:59:45,390 --> 00:59:49,473
Death at the stake! (Energy zaps)

1310
00:59:50,460 --> 00:59:51,610
- I've gotta warn them!

1311
00:59:52,471 --> 00:59:55,388
(Fingers punching)

1312
01:00:05,839 --> 01:00:08,797
- This, this is embarrassing, but my voice,

1313
01:00:08,880 --> 01:00:10,150
something has happened to my voice.

1314
01:00:10,233 --> 01:00:12,097
I wanna know whether or not my throat

1315
01:00:12,180 --> 01:00:14,423
is covered on my insurance policy!

1316
01:00:14,506 --> 01:00:17,256
(Pages rustling)

1317
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:20,947
- Is it an infection?

1318
01:00:21,030 --> 01:00:23,124
You seen a doctor?

1319
01:00:23,207 --> 01:00:25,220
- What, what did you say?

1320
01:00:25,303 --> 01:00:26,317
I didn't catch that.

1321
01:00:26,400 --> 01:00:29,527
- I'm sorry, something's
happened to my mouth too.

1322
01:00:29,610 --> 01:00:31,029
I think it's a spasm.

1323
01:00:31,112 --> 01:00:32,616
I'll have to have it looked at.

1324
01:00:32,699 --> 01:00:34,657
- Steve, you're gonna think I'm crazy.

1325
01:00:34,740 --> 01:00:36,457
But this isn't an infection.

1326
01:00:36,540 --> 01:00:38,077
It isn't anything medical.

1327
01:00:38,160 --> 01:00:40,072
It's a spell!

1328
01:00:40,155 --> 01:00:42,307
- A spell? - Yes, yes.

1329
01:00:42,390 --> 01:00:45,307
This woman claiming to be a
witch cast a spell on my voice

1330
01:00:45,390 --> 01:00:47,407
so I would sound silly.

1331
01:00:47,490 --> 01:00:48,637
I didn't believe her at first.

1332
01:00:48,720 --> 01:00:52,228
I thought she was an escaped
lunatic, but now I believe her.

1333
01:00:52,311 --> 01:00:55,864
- My god, that's what happened to me too.

1334
01:00:55,947 --> 01:01:00,247
Was her name hepzibah Crowley?

1335
01:01:00,330 --> 01:01:03,697
- Yes, I think that was the name she said.

1336
01:01:03,780 --> 01:01:05,894
She did this to you, why?

1337
01:01:05,977 --> 01:01:08,294
- I brought her back to life.

1338
01:01:08,377 --> 01:01:09,690
- [Sam] What?

1339
01:01:09,773 --> 01:01:12,858
- I have this client, the coukos family.

1340
01:01:12,941 --> 01:01:16,429
I met this Jasper coukos,
and I sold him a policy.

1341
01:01:16,512 --> 01:01:19,507
He calls me one day and
asked me how to raise the dead.

1342
01:01:19,590 --> 01:01:22,051
I think this guy's crazy so
I just told him the first thing

1343
01:01:22,134 --> 01:01:24,051
that pops into my mind.

1344
01:01:25,190 --> 01:01:28,927
- The coukos, they're
connected with this witch?

1345
01:01:29,010 --> 01:01:31,177
She's a menace to the community.

1346
01:01:31,260 --> 01:01:33,277
We must do something.

1347
01:01:33,360 --> 01:01:34,110
- What are you gonna do?

1348
01:01:34,193 --> 01:01:36,907
You couldn't have anybody
arrested for witchcraft nowadays.

1349
01:01:36,990 --> 01:01:39,037
No, she needs to be treated on terms

1350
01:01:39,120 --> 01:01:40,370
she's more familiar with.

1351
01:01:41,640 --> 01:01:44,647
- You mean a lynch mob?

1352
01:01:44,730 --> 01:01:46,200
No, no, we can't sink to that.

1353
01:01:46,283 --> 01:01:49,308
- No, I'm saying that if we
treat her with regular means,

1354
01:01:49,391 --> 01:01:51,157
we're not gonna get anywhere.

1355
01:01:51,240 --> 01:01:53,227
You wanna go around
talking like a cartoon character

1356
01:01:53,310 --> 01:01:54,060
for the rest of your life?

1357
01:01:54,143 --> 01:01:55,297
- No!

1358
01:01:55,380 --> 01:01:57,513
- Destroy the witch, destroy the curse.

1359
01:01:59,347 --> 01:02:02,253
- Well, she's already legally dead.

1360
01:02:03,360 --> 01:02:04,237
We need help.

1361
01:02:04,320 --> 01:02:06,247
You know people willing to help us?

1362
01:02:06,330 --> 01:02:09,577
- Oh, it's never been
too difficult to find people

1363
01:02:09,660 --> 01:02:12,244
who would like to do this sort of thing.

1364
01:02:12,327 --> 01:02:14,587
(Suspenseful music)

1365
01:02:14,670 --> 01:02:16,613
- Here's the phone, Jeff. - Thank you.

1366
01:02:18,531 --> 01:02:21,891
(Suspenseful music continues)

1367
01:02:21,974 --> 01:02:24,667
(Buttons punching)

1368
01:02:24,750 --> 01:02:26,947
Hello, ma, this is Jeff.

1369
01:02:27,030 --> 01:02:28,683
Listen, the witch was here.

1370
01:02:30,120 --> 01:02:30,953
You know?

1371
01:02:31,830 --> 01:02:33,787
Jasper brought her back?

1372
01:02:33,870 --> 01:02:35,377
And he's out there.

1373
01:02:35,460 --> 01:02:37,927
Listen, ma, she's coming there to get him.

1374
01:02:38,010 --> 01:02:40,597
He's the last sane loon.

1375
01:02:40,680 --> 01:02:42,037
Get out of there now!

1376
01:02:42,120 --> 01:02:43,323
- Okay, Jeff.

1377
01:02:46,740 --> 01:02:48,157
- What are you gonna do with us?

1378
01:02:48,240 --> 01:02:52,717
- [Hepzibah] I am going to
take this one, this Jasper,

1379
01:02:52,800 --> 01:02:57,067
and tie him to a tree
and burn him to death.

1380
01:02:57,150 --> 01:02:58,807
- Well, that doesn't sound
like a very sane course

1381
01:02:58,890 --> 01:03:00,247
of action to me.

1382
01:03:00,330 --> 01:03:01,567
- We'll stop you.

1383
01:03:01,650 --> 01:03:03,277
You'll have to kill us too!

1384
01:03:03,360 --> 01:03:06,067
- [Hepzibah] Oh, I plan to.

1385
01:03:06,150 --> 01:03:07,717
- Stop giving her suggestions.

1386
01:03:07,800 --> 01:03:10,687
- But first you will help me kill this one.

1387
01:03:10,770 --> 01:03:11,857
- Ha!

1388
01:03:11,940 --> 01:03:13,987
What is this, 17th century humor?

1389
01:03:14,070 --> 01:03:16,177
- We'd have to be as crazy as Jeff is.

1390
01:03:16,260 --> 01:03:17,893
- You will gladly help.

1391
01:03:20,262 --> 01:03:22,762
(Eerie music)

1392
01:03:24,230 --> 01:03:25,623
- Of course, we will.

1393
01:03:26,460 --> 01:03:30,877
I haven't set anybody
on fire in simply ages.

1394
01:03:30,960 --> 01:03:33,787
- Yes, Jasper, it'll be fun.

1395
01:03:33,870 --> 01:03:35,947
Burning at the stake is so romantic.

1396
01:03:36,030 --> 01:03:38,493
- It sounds hazardous to me.

1397
01:03:40,774 --> 01:03:43,774
(Suspenseful music)

1398
01:03:45,427 --> 01:03:47,797
- Now, Jeff, I'm going to
prove to you once and for all

1399
01:03:47,880 --> 01:03:49,387
that there was no witch at your house

1400
01:03:49,470 --> 01:03:50,377
threatening your family.

1401
01:03:50,460 --> 01:03:53,047
- Doctor, I'll only be too
happy to be wrong about this.

1402
01:03:53,130 --> 01:03:54,427
But for now, let's just hurry.

1403
01:03:54,510 --> 01:03:55,410
- All right, Jeff.

1404
01:04:00,694 --> 01:04:03,444
(Car door bangs)

1405
01:04:05,544 --> 01:04:07,297
(Car door bangs)

1406
01:04:07,380 --> 01:04:08,827
Oh, I'm sorry, Jeff.

1407
01:04:08,910 --> 01:04:10,717
I forgot to leave word at the front desk.

1408
01:04:10,800 --> 01:04:11,677
I'll only be a minute.

1409
01:04:11,760 --> 01:04:12,937
- No, we can't wait!

1410
01:04:13,020 --> 01:04:14,041
We've gotta get to my house.

1411
01:04:14,124 --> 01:04:17,437
- Jeff, I have other patients
who need me as much as you do.

1412
01:04:17,520 --> 01:04:20,078
I have to let the staff know
where I am in case I'm needed.

1413
01:04:20,161 --> 01:04:23,364
- No, this is more important!
- I'll be right back.

1414
01:04:23,447 --> 01:04:26,283
- My whole family could
be wiped out by then!

1415
01:04:28,470 --> 01:04:29,303
The keys.

1416
01:04:30,810 --> 01:04:32,917
Okay, Jeff, pull yourself together.

1417
01:04:33,000 --> 01:04:34,987
It doesn't matter what the car looks like,

1418
01:04:35,070 --> 01:04:37,237
just as long as it gets you there.

1419
01:04:37,320 --> 01:04:39,370
And I'm not waiting for her to come back.

1420
01:04:40,315 --> 01:04:44,403
(Playful carnival music)

1421
01:04:44,486 --> 01:04:46,799
(Car door slams)

1422
01:04:46,882 --> 01:04:50,299
(Playful carnival music)

1423
01:04:54,750 --> 01:04:56,673
Not bad, I can live with this.

1424
01:05:00,687 --> 01:05:02,857
(Car door bangs)

1425
01:05:02,940 --> 01:05:05,741
(Car engine revs)

1426
01:05:05,824 --> 01:05:10,824
(Clown chattering comically)
(Instrument clanging)

1427
01:05:19,047 --> 01:05:22,747
- (Laughs) Now you of the loon blood.

1428
01:05:22,830 --> 01:05:25,387
You shall suffer as I did.

1429
01:05:25,470 --> 01:05:26,853
- This is highly irregular.

1430
01:05:30,450 --> 01:05:32,251
- Hello, judge, it's me.

1431
01:05:32,334 --> 01:05:33,637
I found her, yeah.

1432
01:05:33,720 --> 01:05:35,257
She's just about to murder Jasper coukos.

1433
01:05:35,340 --> 01:05:37,567
You go get the boys,
I'll try and hold her off.

1434
01:05:37,650 --> 01:05:40,117
- You know, this won't
look good on a resume.

1435
01:05:40,200 --> 01:05:42,007
- Once you have expired,

1436
01:05:42,090 --> 01:05:45,127
I will be able to go back
to my grave in peace.

1437
01:05:45,210 --> 01:05:47,377
- Oh, please take us with you

1438
01:05:47,460 --> 01:05:50,317
so we may serve you in the afterlife!

1439
01:05:50,400 --> 01:05:52,777
- You wish to follow me into hell?

1440
01:05:52,860 --> 01:05:54,547
- We'll wear light clothing.

1441
01:05:54,630 --> 01:05:57,487
- Yes, I've got this
darling little cotton dress

1442
01:05:57,570 --> 01:05:59,587
I've only worn once.

1443
01:05:59,670 --> 01:06:02,673
- [Hepzibah] Enough,
slaves, who has a match?

1444
01:06:03,570 --> 01:06:04,563
- Not me.

1445
01:06:05,490 --> 01:06:06,967
- Me either.

1446
01:06:07,050 --> 01:06:08,047
- Well, don't look at me.

1447
01:06:08,130 --> 01:06:09,806
Personally, I think you've
gone beyond the bounds

1448
01:06:09,889 --> 01:06:11,317
of good taste.

1449
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:12,333
- Stop, wait!

1450
01:06:13,213 --> 01:06:16,237
- It is you, the small-mouthed one.

1451
01:06:16,320 --> 01:06:18,307
- Will you permit me to speak normally?

1452
01:06:18,390 --> 01:06:19,777
- Oh, very well.

1453
01:06:19,860 --> 01:06:22,162
But briefly will I lift the spell.

1454
01:06:22,245 --> 01:06:24,667
(Eerie music)

1455
01:06:24,750 --> 01:06:26,897
- Oh, thank you, thank you.

1456
01:06:26,980 --> 01:06:28,747
Oh, I can speak again.

1457
01:06:28,830 --> 01:06:30,907
Listen, it occurred to me when you said

1458
01:06:30,990 --> 01:06:32,257
all the power was in your eyes

1459
01:06:32,340 --> 01:06:35,001
that a conscientious witch like you

1460
01:06:35,084 --> 01:06:37,207
should have eye insurance.

1461
01:06:37,290 --> 01:06:39,127
- What nonsense is this?

1462
01:06:39,210 --> 01:06:40,177
- Oh, I'd listened to Steve.

1463
01:06:40,260 --> 01:06:41,874
He sold me a great policy.

1464
01:06:41,957 --> 01:06:45,697
By the way, Steve, am I
covered for loss due to fire?

1465
01:06:45,780 --> 01:06:48,097
- I think it's time you
seriously considered

1466
01:06:48,180 --> 01:06:51,559
catastrophic events, such
as impaired vision, blindness,

1467
01:06:51,642 --> 01:06:53,137
itchy, watery eyes.

1468
01:06:53,220 --> 01:06:55,297
Now, with this policy, you're
covered for the following.

1469
01:06:55,380 --> 01:06:57,187
For the insured's accidental
loss of the following,

1470
01:06:57,270 --> 01:06:59,257
we pay the following amounts.

1471
01:06:59,340 --> 01:07:02,437
Loss of life, twice the amount.

1472
01:07:02,520 --> 01:07:03,967
Loss of feet.

1473
01:07:04,050 --> 01:07:06,967
Sight in both eyes.

1474
01:07:07,050 --> 01:07:10,383
One hand, one foot.

1475
01:07:11,220 --> 01:07:15,080
One hand and the sight of one eye.

1476
01:07:17,381 --> 01:07:19,947
One foot, one hand.

1477
01:07:22,440 --> 01:07:25,593
Loss of one eye.

1478
01:07:26,460 --> 01:07:29,883
On rye with Mayo on the side.

1479
01:07:30,900 --> 01:07:32,047
Asleep, are you?

1480
01:07:32,130 --> 01:07:33,922
Ah, too bad.

1481
01:07:34,005 --> 01:07:36,393
Mm, never underestimate
the power of boredom.

1482
01:07:38,042 --> 01:07:38,993
- What happened?

1483
01:07:39,076 --> 01:07:41,167
- How did we get out here?

1484
01:07:41,250 --> 01:07:43,117
- What did you do to her?

1485
01:07:43,200 --> 01:07:44,617
- Help me tie her to this tree.

1486
01:07:44,700 --> 01:07:46,717
- Oh, finish telling us
about that policy, Steve.

1487
01:07:46,800 --> 01:07:47,732
- Shut up.

1488
01:07:47,815 --> 01:07:52,815
(Townspeople shouting) (Suspenseful music)

1489
01:07:58,276 --> 01:07:59,107
- We're here, Steve.

1490
01:07:59,190 --> 01:08:01,207
- I put her in a trance, my way.

1491
01:08:01,290 --> 01:08:02,377
Are the boys here to do the job?

1492
01:08:02,460 --> 01:08:03,469
- Yes, they're ready.

1493
01:08:03,552 --> 01:08:04,994
But Steve, your voice, it's normal.

1494
01:08:05,077 --> 01:08:07,777
- Oh yeah, I got her to
lift the curse temporarily.

1495
01:08:07,860 --> 01:08:09,311
But don't worry, once she's dead,

1496
01:08:09,394 --> 01:08:11,227
everything will be back to normal.

1497
01:08:11,310 --> 01:08:13,758
- What makes you think
everything will be back to normal?

1498
01:08:13,841 --> 01:08:15,517
What are you gonna do to her?

1499
01:08:15,600 --> 01:08:18,907
- We're gonna serve up
some old-fashioned justice.

1500
01:08:18,990 --> 01:08:21,727
The right way to kill a witch
is to burn her at the stake!

1501
01:08:21,810 --> 01:08:22,560
Right, boys?

1502
01:08:22,643 --> 01:08:25,897
- [Townspeople] Yeah, yeah, yeah!

1503
01:08:25,980 --> 01:08:28,657
- Oh, I thought we were
going to burn her like a steak.

1504
01:08:28,740 --> 01:08:31,177
- Oh, I thought we were going to burn her

1505
01:08:31,260 --> 01:08:33,127
as one would a steak.

1506
01:08:33,210 --> 01:08:35,573
- I didn't bring any steak,
all I brought was fish.

1507
01:08:35,656 --> 01:08:37,777
- What kind of a lynch mob are you?

1508
01:08:37,860 --> 01:08:38,610
- Come on, judge.

1509
01:08:38,693 --> 01:08:40,443
We'll do the job ourselves.

1510
01:08:43,080 --> 01:08:44,227
- No, Steve, wait!

1511
01:08:44,310 --> 01:08:45,534
We can't do it this way.

1512
01:08:45,617 --> 01:08:48,617
This is not the right
way, we're civilized men.

1513
01:08:48,700 --> 01:08:51,107
Here, here, use my lighter.

1514
01:08:52,316 --> 01:08:54,169
- All right, ma, ma! - Here, Jeff.

1515
01:08:54,252 --> 01:08:55,458
- Jeff, how did you get here?

1516
01:08:55,541 --> 01:08:57,367
- You'd never believe me.

1517
01:08:57,450 --> 01:08:58,297
What's going on?

1518
01:08:58,380 --> 01:08:59,703
- They're gonna burn hepzibah.

1519
01:08:59,786 --> 01:09:02,257
- Ah, let her burn, it's been a rough week.

1520
01:09:02,340 --> 01:09:03,991
- We can't, don't you see?

1521
01:09:04,074 --> 01:09:06,817
Hepzibah being dead
isn't gonna break the curse.

1522
01:09:06,900 --> 01:09:08,317
We have to save her.

1523
01:09:08,400 --> 01:09:11,073
If she dies again, we'll
never have another chance.

1524
01:09:12,141 --> 01:09:16,237
(Townspeople chattering)

1525
01:09:16,320 --> 01:09:17,227
- Excuse me.

1526
01:09:17,310 --> 01:09:19,778
Mob, oh mob, may I
have your attention please?

1527
01:09:19,861 --> 01:09:22,837
Now you say that it's
right to burn witches.

1528
01:09:22,920 --> 01:09:24,397
Does that mean all witches?

1529
01:09:24,480 --> 01:09:26,527
- [Townspeople] Yeah, yeah!

1530
01:09:26,610 --> 01:09:28,807
- Yes, I'm judge and I say it's right!

1531
01:09:28,890 --> 01:09:29,677
- Well, in that case,

1532
01:09:29,760 --> 01:09:32,047
I'd like to point out
that this man is a witch.

1533
01:09:32,130 --> 01:09:35,017
He turned my cat into an avocado!

1534
01:09:35,100 --> 01:09:37,009
- That's, that's not true.

1535
01:09:37,092 --> 01:09:37,842
(Townspeople chattering)

1536
01:09:37,925 --> 01:09:39,427
- Oh, I get it.

1537
01:09:39,510 --> 01:09:40,503
This woman is a witch!

1538
01:09:40,586 --> 01:09:41,527
(Townspeople shout)

1539
01:09:41,610 --> 01:09:44,673
She has the power to
turn water into ice cubes!

1540
01:09:44,756 --> 01:09:46,237
- No, not me.

1541
01:09:46,320 --> 01:09:47,857
- Yes, and I happen to know

1542
01:09:47,940 --> 01:09:50,306
this woman plays bridge with armadillos!

1543
01:09:50,389 --> 01:09:54,157
- I never play bridge with armadillos.

1544
01:09:54,240 --> 01:09:57,517
- [Jeff] I saw this man
riding Satan's bicycle!

1545
01:09:57,600 --> 01:09:59,767
- I never rode Satan's bicycle!

1546
01:09:59,850 --> 01:10:01,627
- There's too many witches out there.

1547
01:10:01,710 --> 01:10:02,575
What are we gonna do?

1548
01:10:02,658 --> 01:10:03,937
We don't have that much kindling.

1549
01:10:04,020 --> 01:10:06,470
- Judge, I heard you say last
year that you'd sell your soul

1550
01:10:06,553 --> 01:10:08,467
for some world series tickets.

1551
01:10:08,550 --> 01:10:10,187
- Yeah, that's right, and I saw him there.

1552
01:10:10,270 --> 01:10:12,155
I saw him in the stands on TV.

1553
01:10:12,238 --> 01:10:15,070
- It wasn't me, I wasn't there!

1554
01:10:15,153 --> 01:10:17,512
- (Screams) I confess!

1555
01:10:17,595 --> 01:10:19,740
I'm possessed by Satan!

1556
01:10:19,823 --> 01:10:23,619
Recipes for quiche manifest
themselves on my skin!

1557
01:10:23,702 --> 01:10:24,628
(Citizen shouts)

1558
01:10:24,711 --> 01:10:27,037
(Townspeople chattering)

1559
01:10:27,120 --> 01:10:29,467
- This is getting out of hand,
maybe we should knock it off.

1560
01:10:29,550 --> 01:10:31,057
- Let her go, Sam!

1561
01:10:31,140 --> 01:10:31,973
- All right.

1562
01:10:33,090 --> 01:10:35,193
Listen, folks, folks!

1563
01:10:36,330 --> 01:10:38,317
There seems to have been a big mistake.

1564
01:10:38,400 --> 01:10:40,297
We wanna thank you for coming out though.

1565
01:10:40,380 --> 01:10:42,217
You've been a great mob, really.

1566
01:10:42,300 --> 01:10:44,227
Next time we need a
mindless mass of people,

1567
01:10:44,310 --> 01:10:45,683
we'll be sure to call you.

1568
01:10:45,766 --> 01:10:47,757
(Townspeople groaning)

1569
01:10:47,840 --> 01:10:51,257
(Townspeople chattering)

1570
01:10:53,174 --> 01:10:54,944
- Ah, there we are.

1571
01:10:55,027 --> 01:10:56,377
Hepzibah, wake up! (Fingers snapping)

1572
01:10:56,460 --> 01:10:57,603
Wake up, hepzibah!

1573
01:10:59,700 --> 01:11:00,727
- What happened?

1574
01:11:00,810 --> 01:11:02,854
- Well, Steve here subdued you into sleep

1575
01:11:02,937 --> 01:11:05,407
with some boring insurance jargon.

1576
01:11:05,490 --> 01:11:08,827
Well, and then this mob here
was going to burn you to death.

1577
01:11:08,910 --> 01:11:09,967
- Why didn't they?

1578
01:11:10,050 --> 01:11:11,227
- Well, we stopped them.

1579
01:11:11,310 --> 01:11:14,009
- You, the Coukos's?

1580
01:11:14,092 --> 01:11:16,417
Loon blood saved my life?

1581
01:11:16,500 --> 01:11:17,250
- Yes, we have.

1582
01:11:17,333 --> 01:11:19,837
And I must say that
you've behaved very badly.

1583
01:11:19,920 --> 01:11:21,547
You've behaved abominably.

1584
01:11:21,630 --> 01:11:23,737
And I am never going to
bring you back to life again.

1585
01:11:23,820 --> 01:11:25,477
- You're right.

1586
01:11:25,560 --> 01:11:29,317
I've been an awful nuisance
these last few hundred years.

1587
01:11:29,400 --> 01:11:31,687
I should go back to the grave.

1588
01:11:31,770 --> 01:11:33,367
- How about removing the curse?

1589
01:11:33,450 --> 01:11:34,807
- Very well.

1590
01:11:34,890 --> 01:11:36,757
From what I have witnessed,

1591
01:11:36,840 --> 01:11:41,493
'tis punishment enough
just to live in this age.

1592
01:11:42,600 --> 01:11:45,847
Loon blood, I cleanse you.

1593
01:11:45,930 --> 01:11:48,027
The curse is no more!

1594
01:11:48,110 --> 01:11:50,860
(Mystical music)

1595
01:11:58,170 --> 01:11:59,819
- You're all normal.

1596
01:11:59,902 --> 01:12:00,819
I'm normal!

1597
01:12:02,527 --> 01:12:03,831
- Ah!

1598
01:12:03,914 --> 01:12:06,914
(Suspenseful music)

1599
01:12:12,914 --> 01:12:15,090
Oh, there he is!

1600
01:12:15,173 --> 01:12:18,008
- Ma, this is Kerry, my fiancee.

1601
01:12:18,091 --> 01:12:19,672
- Hi, nice to meet you. - Congratulations.

1602
01:12:19,755 --> 01:12:21,390
Jeff's told me all about you.

1603
01:12:21,473 --> 01:12:23,091
This is Jeff's brother Jasper.

1604
01:12:23,174 --> 01:12:24,391
- Hi. - Hello, Kerry, right?

1605
01:12:24,474 --> 01:12:26,197
- Yes. - Hi, Jasper.

1606
01:12:26,280 --> 01:12:28,237
- Come on in, I've got the coffee ready.

1607
01:12:28,320 --> 01:12:29,655
How was your trip? - Oh, it was great.

1608
01:12:29,738 --> 01:12:32,905
- Oh, good. - We got a wedding to plan.

1609
01:12:34,115 --> 01:12:37,115
(People chattering)

1610
01:12:44,673 --> 01:12:48,256
(Solemn harpsichord music)

